  "instruction_layer": {
    "inline": [
      "The compiled runtime guide is authoritative for the next legal action.",
      "Observer owns orchestration, child-contract prefill, dispatch, merge, reconcile, and close-ready evidence only.",
            "mf_sub workers own read receipt, startup, graph trace, implementation, worker commit, finish-time attestation, and finish gate evidence in their assigned worktree/fence.",
      "QA owns QA graph context and independent verification evidence; observer must not write or reconstruct QA evidence.",
      "Prefer explicit parallel child contracts with owned_files fences before dispatching workers.",
      "For observer_reconcile, first run graph_current_full_reconcile with a reconcile-only route whose canonical task_id comes from the dispatched runtime_context.task_id; then submit the ContractRuntime observer_reconcile line with the child contract execution route. These route scopes are not interchangeable.",
      "Copy only observer_session_id, route_token_ref, backlog_id, contract_execution_id, runtime_context_id, task_id, and target_project_root between the observer guide and current-full reconcile. Never copy a raw route token, and accept reconcile evidence only from the live authoritative snapshot returned by graph_snapshot_store.current_full_reconcile_state."
    ],
    "refs": []
  },
